cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.HC, cs.MM, cs.IR 

Reasoning: 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on analyzing the social relationships and dynamics of user donations in a crowdsourced video system. 
- cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences) is also likely as the paper examines the impact of user donations on community engagement and success of the system. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is relevant as the paper discusses the features developed by the video system to boost community engagement and user donations. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is relevant as the paper focuses on a crowdsourced video system and the dataset includes information on video content. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is less likely but still possible as the paper uses machine-learned classifiers and network representation learning models to predict the destinations of user donations.
